commit.message: No need to wait such a long time.
Add gnu source in Cask file.

Add a trailing newline to the index to make sure.

This is related to ed8176f9a01888527b1f6719c66a59c3d62fb55d.
Test both index command and --index option.
Elnode does not automatically start anymore.
The variable debug-on-entry does not exist.
Use docstring from functions in commander schema.

Prepend newline in index string.

This is because of a package.el bug where it searches for the contents,
which is at the end of the headers. Without the newline, and end-of-file
error occurs.

This does not seem to happen all the time and I have not found a way to
continuously reproduce it. Though I have seen that it behaves
differently on various web servers.

Fix package routes

Packages do not have directory separators in their names.

Convert to multibyte string before sending

Unibyte strings apparently confuse Elnode and cause Tar archives to fail.
Inhibit the default server during byte-compilation
